judge.verdict_format:
Output ONLY a JSON object in this exact schema (no extra text before or after):
{
  "scores": {
    "pro":    {"logic": 0, "evidence": 0, "rebuttal_quality": 0, "relevance": 0, "clarity": 0, "citation_quality": 0, "consistency": 0, "total": 0},
    "contra": {"logic": 0, "evidence": 0, "rebuttal_quality": 0, "relevance": 0, "clarity": 0, "citation_quality": 0, "consistency": 0, "total": 0}
  },
  "reasoning": {"pro": "2 sentences max", "contra": "2 sentences max"},
  "winner": "Pro"
}
Scoring ranges: logic 0-20, evidence 0-20, rebuttal_quality 0-20, relevance 0-10, clarity 0-10, citation_quality 0-10, consistency 0-10. total = sum of all seven fields (max 100). Set winner to exactly "Pro" or "Contra". After the JSON, on a new line write: WINNER: Pro  (or WINNER: Contra).
